creator: Eric Mackay
description: LibriVox volunteers bring you 14 recordings of A Thunderstorm at Night by Eric Mackay. This was the Weekly Poetry project for May 29, 2016. Read in English by Bruce Kachuk; Brian Darby; David Lawrence; Esther ben Simonides; Newgatenovelist; Garth Burton; GabrielleC; Greg Giordano; Lee Ann Howlett; Leonard Wilson; Maria Kasper; Matthew Datcher; SkyAlbatross and Tomas Peter. George Eric Mackay was an English minor poet, now remembered as the sponging half-brother of Marie Corelli, the best-selling novelist. Mackay and Corelli, born Mary Mackay, were the children of Charles Mackay, by different mothers. As a poet he is described as "execrable", and reliant on Corelli's promotion of his works. Mackay achieved some reputation in his time for Letters of a Violinist (1886). It sold 35,000 copies; he repaid Corelli's efforts by implying he wrote her novels. ( Wikipedia) For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.
